comment_data.body: If this is going to be addressed it will probably be by the Dart Analyzer, which does all the static error analysis for Dart and Flutter code. Perhaps @bwilkerson could say whether this issue ought to be moved to the analyzer project?
It sounds like this might be an issue in the Dart plugin (and would be best to track in youtrack)?
I suggested youtrack already and they sent him back :-/

I am sorry, I used Google Tracker (don't know if that is also called youtrack or youtrack is a separate thing). 

Actually I opened Android Studio under Help/Report an issue section, they took me to a website of Google Tracker and there I filled in the information and the replied they sent me was shown above.
I see. can you post a link? Youtrack would be https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/ (as posted in my first comment above)

I am sorry due to some issues (internally) I can't share Google Tracker link, however I just posted a new issue to youtrack on your say and here is the link for that. 
https://youtrack.jetbrains.com/issue/IDEA-198218
This is tracked as a Dart plugin issue, 198218
I can't see any link of Dart plugin issue 198218.
@dark-chocolate That's the link you posted in your previous comment.

@zoechi Got it! Thanks, but that issue hasn't been solved on youtrack. Does it mean if it will be solved it will only be solved on youtrack and github can't do anything in my issue. Only youtrack is the last resort?
